      "reason": "Regulatory context matters here: if compliance allows provisional registration with deferred KYC, an async queue is needed (new infrastructure). If compliance requires synchronous KYC, the team must accept they cannot meet 99.95% and should adjust their SLA target or add a second KYC provider. Either path requires a product/compliance decision before shipping.",
      "routed_to": "Coach K"
    },
    {
      "type": "missing_observability",
      "issue": "Cannot distinguish Onfido outage from legitimate KYC rejection in metrics",
      "reason": "On-call engineer at 3am sees kyc_checks_total spiking with failures. Are users committing fraud, or is Onfido down? Without a metric that separates 'provider error' from 'verification rejected', incident response is guesswork. Add labels to kyc_checks_total: result=provider_error|rejected|approved|timeout.",
      "routed_to": "Coach K"
    }
  ],

  "confidence": {
    "level": 85,
    "high_confidence_areas": [
      "SLA arithmetic: 99.95% target is unachievable with a 99.9% synchronous hard dependency and no fallback — this is a mathematical fact",
      "Cascading failure risk from missing circuit breaker under Onfido degradation",
      "Observability gap in distinguishing outage from rejection"
